33class GenerateLevelFilesBriefTest : public testing::Test {
34 public:
35 std::vector<FileMetaData*> files_;
36 LevelFilesBrief file_level_;
37 Arena arena_;
38
39 GenerateLevelFilesBriefTest() = default;
40
41 ~GenerateLevelFilesBriefTest() override {
42 for (size_t i = 0; i < files_.size(); i++) {
43 delete files_[i];
44 }
45 }
46
47 void Add(const char* smallest, const char* largest,
48 SequenceNumber smallest_seq = 100,
49 SequenceNumber largest_seq = 100) {
50 FileMetaData* f = new FileMetaData(
51 files_.size() + 1, 0, 0,
52 InternalKey(smallest, smallest_seq, kTypeValue),
53 InternalKey(largest, largest_seq, kTypeValue), smallest_seq,
54 largest_seq, /* marked_for_compact */ false, Temperature::kUnknown,
55 kInvalidBlobFileNumber, kUnknownOldestAncesterTime,
56 kUnknownFileCreationTime, kUnknownEpochNumber, kUnknownFileChecksum,
57 kUnknownFileChecksumFuncName, kNullUniqueId64x2, 0, 0,
58 /* user_defined_timestamps_persisted */ true);
59 files_.push_back(f);
60 }
61
62 int Compare() {
63 int diff = 0;
64 for (size_t i = 0; i < files_.size(); i++) {
65 if (file_level_.files[i].fd.GetNumber() != files_[i]->fd.GetNumber()) {
66 diff++;
67 }
68 }
69 return diff;
70 }
71};
72
73TEST_F(GenerateLevelFilesBriefTest, Empty) {
74 DoGenerateLevelFilesBrief(&file_level_, files_, &arena_);
75 ASSERT_EQ(0u, file_level_.num_files);
76 ASSERT_EQ(0, Compare());
77}
78
79TEST_F(GenerateLevelFilesBriefTest, Single) {
80 Add("p", "q");
81 DoGenerateLevelFilesBrief(&file_level_, files_, &arena_);
82 ASSERT_EQ(1u, file_level_.num_files);
83 ASSERT_EQ(0, Compare());
84}
85
86TEST_F(GenerateLevelFilesBriefTest, Multiple) {
87 Add("150", "200");
88 Add("200", "250");
89 Add("300", "350");
90 Add("400", "450");
91 DoGenerateLevelFilesBrief(&file_level_, files_, &arena_);
92 ASSERT_EQ(4u, file_level_.num_files);
93 ASSERT_EQ(0, Compare());
94}

96class CountingLogger : public Logger {
97 public:
98 CountingLogger() : log_count(0) {}
99 using Logger::Logv;
100 void Logv(const char* /*format*/, va_list /*ap*/) override { log_count++; }
101 int log_count;
102};
103
104Options GetOptionsWithNumLevels(int num_levels,
105 std::shared_ptr<CountingLogger> logger) {
106 Options opt;
107 opt.num_levels = num_levels;
108 opt.info_log = logger;
109 return opt;
110}

112class VersionStorageInfoTestBase : public testing::Test {
113 public:
114 const Comparator* ucmp_;
115 InternalKeyComparator icmp_;
116 std::shared_ptr<CountingLogger> logger_;
117 Options options_;
118 ImmutableOptions ioptions_;
119 MutableCFOptions mutable_cf_options_;
120 VersionStorageInfo vstorage_;
121
122 InternalKey GetInternalKey(const char* ukey,
123 SequenceNumber smallest_seq = 100) {
124 return InternalKey(ukey, smallest_seq, kTypeValue);
125 }
126
127 explicit VersionStorageInfoTestBase(const Comparator* ucmp)
128 : ucmp_(ucmp),
129 icmp_(ucmp_),
130 logger_(new CountingLogger()),
131 options_(GetOptionsWithNumLevels(6, logger_)),
132 ioptions_(options_),
133 mutable_cf_options_(options_),
134 vstorage_(&icmp_, ucmp_, 6, kCompactionStyleLevel,
135 /*src_vstorage=*/nullptr,
136 /*_force_consistency_checks=*/false,
137 EpochNumberRequirement::kMustPresent, ioptions_.clock,
138 mutable_cf_options_.bottommost_file_compaction_delay,
139 OffpeakTimeOption()) {}
140
141 ~VersionStorageInfoTestBase() override {
142 for (int i = 0; i < vstorage_.num_levels(); ++i) {
143 for (auto* f : vstorage_.LevelFiles(i)) {
144 if (--f->refs == 0) {
145 delete f;
146 }
147 }
148 }
149 }
150
151 void Add(int level, uint32_t file_number, const char* smallest,
152 const char* largest, uint64_t file_size = 0,
153 uint64_t oldest_blob_file_number = kInvalidBlobFileNumber,
154 uint64_t compensated_range_deletion_size = 0) {
155 constexpr SequenceNumber dummy_seq = 0;
156
157 Add(level, file_number, GetInternalKey(smallest, dummy_seq),
158 GetInternalKey(largest, dummy_seq), file_size, oldest_blob_file_number,
159 compensated_range_deletion_size);
160 }
161
162 void Add(int level, uint32_t file_number, const InternalKey& smallest,
163 const InternalKey& largest, uint64_t file_size = 0,
164 uint64_t oldest_blob_file_number = kInvalidBlobFileNumber,
165 uint64_t compensated_range_deletion_size = 0) {
166 assert(level < vstorage_.num_levels());
167 FileMetaData* f = new FileMetaData(
168 file_number, 0, file_size, smallest, largest, /* smallest_seq */ 0,
169 /* largest_seq */ 0, /* marked_for_compact */ false,
170 Temperature::kUnknown, oldest_blob_file_number,
171 kUnknownOldestAncesterTime, kUnknownFileCreationTime,
172 kUnknownEpochNumber, kUnknownFileChecksum, kUnknownFileChecksumFuncName,
173 kNullUniqueId64x2, compensated_range_deletion_size, 0,
174 /* user_defined_timestamps_persisted */ true);
175 vstorage_.AddFile(level, f);
176 }
177
178 void AddBlob(uint64_t blob_file_number, uint64_t total_blob_count,
179 uint64_t total_blob_bytes,
180 BlobFileMetaData::LinkedSsts linked_ssts,
181 uint64_t garbage_blob_count, uint64_t garbage_blob_bytes) {
182 auto shared_meta = SharedBlobFileMetaData::Create(
183 blob_file_number, total_blob_count, total_blob_bytes,
184 /* checksum_method */ std::string(),
185 /* checksum_value */ std::string());
186 auto meta =
187 BlobFileMetaData::Create(std::move(shared_meta), std::move(linked_ssts),
188 garbage_blob_count, garbage_blob_bytes);
189
190 vstorage_.AddBlobFile(std::move(meta));
191 }
192
193 void UpdateVersionStorageInfo() {
194 vstorage_.PrepareForVersionAppend(ioptions_, mutable_cf_options_);
195 vstorage_.SetFinalized();
196 }
197
198 std::string GetOverlappingFiles(int level, const InternalKey& begin,
199 const InternalKey& end) {
200 std::vector<FileMetaData*> inputs;
201 vstorage_.GetOverlappingInputs(level, &begin, &end, &inputs);
202
203 std::string result;
204 for (size_t i = 0; i < inputs.size(); ++i) {
205 if (i > 0) {
206 result += ",";
207 }
208 AppendNumberTo(&result, inputs[i]->fd.GetNumber());
209 }
210 return result;
211 }
212};

398TEST_F(VersionStorageInfoTest, MaxBytesForLevelDynamicWithLargeL0_2) {
399 ioptions_.level_compaction_dynamic_level_bytes = true;
400 mutable_cf_options_.max_bytes_for_level_base = 10000;
401 mutable_cf_options_.max_bytes_for_level_multiplier = 5;
402 mutable_cf_options_.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger = 4;
403
404 Add(0, 11U, "1", "2", 10000U);
405 Add(0, 12U, "1", "2", 10000U);
406 Add(0, 13U, "1", "2", 10000U);
407
408 // Level size should be around 10,000, 10,290, 51,450, 257,250
409 Add(5, 4U, "1", "2", 1286250U);
410 Add(4, 5U, "1", "2", 258000U); // unadjusted score 1.003
411 Add(3, 6U, "1", "2", 53000U); // unadjusted score 1.03
412 Add(2, 7U, "1", "2", 20000U); // unadjusted score 1.94
413
414 UpdateVersionStorageInfo();
415
416 ASSERT_EQ(0, logger_->log_count);
417 ASSERT_EQ(1, vstorage_.base_level());
418 ASSERT_EQ(10000U, vstorage_.MaxBytesForLevel(1));
419 ASSERT_EQ(10290U, vstorage_.MaxBytesForLevel(2));
420 ASSERT_EQ(51450U, vstorage_.MaxBytesForLevel(3));
421 ASSERT_EQ(257250U, vstorage_.MaxBytesForLevel(4));
422
423 vstorage_.ComputeCompactionScore(ioptions_, mutable_cf_options_);
424 // Although L2 and l3 have higher unadjusted compaction score, considering
425 // a relatively large L0 being compacted down soon, L4 is picked up for
426 // compaction.
427 // L0 is still picked up for oversizing.
428 ASSERT_EQ(0, vstorage_.CompactionScoreLevel(0));
429 ASSERT_EQ(4, vstorage_.CompactionScoreLevel(1));
430}

432TEST_F(VersionStorageInfoTest, MaxBytesForLevelDynamicWithLargeL0_3) {
433 ioptions_.level_compaction_dynamic_level_bytes = true;
434 mutable_cf_options_.max_bytes_for_level_base = 20000;
435 mutable_cf_options_.max_bytes_for_level_multiplier = 5;
436 mutable_cf_options_.level0_file_num_compaction_trigger = 5;
437
438 Add(0, 11U, "1", "2", 2500U);
439 Add(0, 12U, "1", "2", 2500U);
440 Add(0, 13U, "1", "2", 2500U);
441 Add(0, 14U, "1", "2", 2500U);
442
443 // Level size should be around 20,000, 53000, 258000
444 Add(5, 4U, "1", "2", 1286250U);
445 Add(4, 5U, "1", "2", 260000U); // Unadjusted score 1.01, adjusted about 4.3
446 Add(3, 6U, "1", "2", 85000U); // Unadjusted score 1.42, adjusted about 11.6
447 Add(2, 7U, "1", "2", 30000); // Unadjusted score 1.5, adjusted about 10.0

456 // Although L2 has higher unadjusted compaction score, considering
457 // a relatively large L0 being compacted down soon, L3 is picked up for
458 // compaction.
459
460 ASSERT_EQ(3, vstorage_.CompactionScoreLevel(0));
461 ASSERT_EQ(2, vstorage_.CompactionScoreLevel(1));
462 ASSERT_EQ(4, vstorage_.CompactionScoreLevel(2));
463}

465TEST_F(VersionStorageInfoTest, DrainUnnecessaryLevel) {
466 ioptions_.level_compaction_dynamic_level_bytes = true;
467 mutable_cf_options_.max_bytes_for_level_base = 1000;
468 mutable_cf_options_.max_bytes_for_level_multiplier = 10;
469
470 // Create a few unnecessary levels.
471 // See if score is calculated correctly.
472 Add(5, 1U, "1", "2", 2000U); // target size 1010000
473 Add(4, 2U, "1", "2", 200U); // target size 101000
474 // Unnecessary levels
475 Add(3, 3U, "1", "2", 100U); // target size 10100
476 // Level 2: target size 1010
477 Add(1, 4U, "1", "2",
478 10U); // target size 1000 = max(base_bytes_min + 1, base_bytes_max)
479
480 UpdateVersionStorageInfo();
481
482 ASSERT_EQ(1, vstorage_.base_level());
483 ASSERT_EQ(1000, vstorage_.MaxBytesForLevel(1));
484 ASSERT_EQ(10100, vstorage_.MaxBytesForLevel(3));
485 vstorage_.ComputeCompactionScore(ioptions_, mutable_cf_options_);
486
487 // Tests that levels 1 and 3 are eligible for compaction.
488 // Levels 1 and 3 are much smaller than target size,
489 // so size does not contribute to a high compaction score.
490 ASSERT_EQ(1, vstorage_.CompactionScoreLevel(0));
491 ASSERT_GT(vstorage_.CompactionScore(0), 10);
492 ASSERT_EQ(3, vstorage_.CompactionScoreLevel(1));
493 ASSERT_GT(vstorage_.CompactionScore(1), 10);
494}

525TEST_F(VersionStorageInfoTest, SingleLevelBottommostData) {
526 // In case of a single level, the oldest L0 file is bottommost. This could be
527 // improved in case the L0 files cover disjoint key-ranges.
528 Add(0 /* level */, 1U /* file_number */, "A" /* smallest */,
529 "Z" /* largest */, 1U /* file_size */);
530 Add(0 /* level */, 2U /* file_number */, "A" /* smallest */,
531 "Z" /* largest */, 1U /* file_size */);
532 Add(0 /* level */, 3U /* file_number */, "0" /* smallest */,
533 "9" /* largest */, 1U /* file_size */);
534
535 UpdateVersionStorageInfo();
536
537 ASSERT_EQ(1, vstorage_.BottommostFiles().size());
538 ASSERT_EQ(0, vstorage_.BottommostFiles()[0].first);
539 ASSERT_EQ(3U, vstorage_.BottommostFiles()[0].second->fd.GetNumber());
540}

542TEST_F(VersionStorageInfoTest, MultiLevelBottommostData) {
543 // In case of multiple levels, the oldest file for a key-range from each L1+
544 // level is bottommost. This could be improved in case an L0 file contains the
545 // oldest data for some range of keys.
546 Add(0 /* level */, 1U /* file_number */, "A" /* smallest */,
547 "Z" /* largest */, 1U /* file_size */);
548 Add(0 /* level */, 2U /* file_number */, "0" /* smallest */,
549 "9" /* largest */, 1U /* file_size */);
550 Add(1 /* level */, 3U /* file_number */, "A" /* smallest */,
551 "D" /* largest */, 1U /* file_size */);
552 Add(2 /* level */, 4U /* file_number */, "E" /* smallest */,
553 "H" /* largest */, 1U /* file_size */);
554 Add(2 /* level */, 5U /* file_number */, "I" /* smallest */,
555 "L" /* largest */, 1U /* file_size */);
556
557 UpdateVersionStorageInfo();
558
559 autovector<std::pair<int, FileMetaData*>> bottommost_files =
560 vstorage_.BottommostFiles();
561 std::sort(bottommost_files.begin(), bottommost_files.end(),
562 [](const std::pair<int, FileMetaData*>& lhs,
563 const std::pair<int, FileMetaData*>& rhs) {
564 assert(lhs.second);
565 assert(rhs.second);
566 return lhs.second->fd.GetNumber() < rhs.second->fd.GetNumber();
567 });
568 ASSERT_EQ(3, bottommost_files.size());
569 ASSERT_EQ(3U, bottommost_files[0].second->fd.GetNumber());
570 ASSERT_EQ(4U, bottommost_files[1].second->fd.GetNumber());
571 ASSERT_EQ(5U, bottommost_files[2].second->fd.GetNumber());
572}

574TEST_F(VersionStorageInfoTest, GetOverlappingInputs) {

646TEST_F(VersionStorageInfoTest, ForcedBlobGCSingleBatch) {
647 // Test the edge case when all blob files are part of the oldest batch.
648 // We have one L0 SST file #1, and four blob files #10, #11, #12, and #13.
649 // The oldest blob file used by SST #1 is blob file #10.
650
651 constexpr int level = 0;
652
653 constexpr uint64_t sst = 1;
654
655 constexpr uint64_t first_blob = 10;
656 constexpr uint64_t second_blob = 11;
657 constexpr uint64_t third_blob = 12;
658 constexpr uint64_t fourth_blob = 13;
659
660 {
661 constexpr char smallest[] = "bar1";
662 constexpr char largest[] = "foo1";
663 constexpr uint64_t file_size = 1000;
664
665 Add(level, sst, smallest, largest, file_size, first_blob);
666 }
667
668 {
669 constexpr uint64_t total_blob_count = 10;
670 constexpr uint64_t total_blob_bytes = 100000;
671 constexpr uint64_t garbage_blob_count = 2;
672 constexpr uint64_t garbage_blob_bytes = 15000;
673
674 AddBlob(first_blob, total_blob_count, total_blob_bytes,
675 BlobFileMetaData::LinkedSsts{sst}, garbage_blob_count,
676 garbage_blob_bytes);
677 }
678
679 {
680 constexpr uint64_t total_blob_count = 4;
681 constexpr uint64_t total_blob_bytes = 400000;
682 constexpr uint64_t garbage_blob_count = 3;
683 constexpr uint64_t garbage_blob_bytes = 235000;
684
685 AddBlob(second_blob, total_blob_count, total_blob_bytes,
686 BlobFileMetaData::LinkedSsts{}, garbage_blob_count,
687 garbage_blob_bytes);
688 }
689
690 {
691 constexpr uint64_t total_blob_count = 20;
692 constexpr uint64_t total_blob_bytes = 1000000;
693 constexpr uint64_t garbage_blob_count = 8;
694 constexpr uint64_t garbage_blob_bytes = 400000;
695
696 AddBlob(third_blob, total_blob_count, total_blob_bytes,
697 BlobFileMetaData::LinkedSsts{}, garbage_blob_count,
698 garbage_blob_bytes);
699 }
700
701 {
702 constexpr uint64_t total_blob_count = 128;
703 constexpr uint64_t total_blob_bytes = 1000000;
704 constexpr uint64_t garbage_blob_count = 67;
705 constexpr uint64_t garbage_blob_bytes = 600000;
706
707 AddBlob(fourth_blob, total_blob_count, total_blob_bytes,
708 BlobFileMetaData::LinkedSsts{}, garbage_blob_count,
709 garbage_blob_bytes);
710 }
711
712 UpdateVersionStorageInfo();
713
714 assert(vstorage_.num_levels() > 0);
715 const auto& level_files = vstorage_.LevelFiles(level);
716
717 assert(level_files.size() == 1);
718 assert(level_files[0] && level_files[0]->fd.GetNumber() == sst);
719
720 // No blob files eligible for GC due to the age cutoff
721
722 {
723 constexpr double age_cutoff = 0.1;
724 constexpr double force_threshold = 0.0;
725 vstorage_.ComputeFilesMarkedForForcedBlobGC(
726 age_cutoff, force_threshold, /*enable_blob_garbage_collection=*/true);
727
728 ASSERT_TRUE(vstorage_.FilesMarkedForForcedBlobGC().empty());
729 }
730
731 // Overall garbage ratio of eligible files is below threshold
732
733 {
734 constexpr double age_cutoff = 1.0;
735 constexpr double force_threshold = 0.6;
736 vstorage_.ComputeFilesMarkedForForcedBlobGC(
737 age_cutoff, force_threshold, /*enable_blob_garbage_collection=*/true);
738
739 ASSERT_TRUE(vstorage_.FilesMarkedForForcedBlobGC().empty());
740 }
741
742 // Overall garbage ratio of eligible files meets threshold
743
744 {
745 constexpr double age_cutoff = 1.0;
746 constexpr double force_threshold = 0.5;
747 vstorage_.ComputeFilesMarkedForForcedBlobGC(
748 age_cutoff, force_threshold, /*enable_blob_garbage_collection=*/true);
749
750 auto ssts_to_be_compacted = vstorage_.FilesMarkedForForcedBlobGC();
751 ASSERT_EQ(ssts_to_be_compacted.size(), 1);
752
753 const autovector<std::pair<int, FileMetaData*>>
754 expected_ssts_to_be_compacted{{level, level_files[0]}};
755
756 ASSERT_EQ(ssts_to_be_compacted[0], expected_ssts_to_be_compacted[0]);
757 }

760TEST_F(VersionStorageInfoTest, ForcedBlobGCMultipleBatches) {
761 // Add three L0 SSTs (1, 2, and 3) and four blob files (10, 11, 12, and 13).
762 // The first two SSTs have the same oldest blob file, namely, the very oldest
763 // one (10), while the third SST's oldest blob file reference points to the
764 // third blob file (12). Thus, the oldest batch of blob files contains the
765 // first two blob files 10 and 11, and assuming they are eligible for GC based
766 // on the age cutoff, compacting away the SSTs 1 and 2 will eliminate them.
767
768 constexpr int level = 0;
769
770 constexpr uint64_t first_sst = 1;
771 constexpr uint64_t second_sst = 2;
772 constexpr uint64_t third_sst = 3;
773

777 constexpr uint64_t fourth_blob = 13;
778
779 {
780 constexpr char smallest[] = "bar1";
781 constexpr char largest[] = "foo1";
782 constexpr uint64_t file_size = 1000;
783
784 Add(level, first_sst, smallest, largest, file_size, first_blob);
785 }
786
787 {
788 constexpr char smallest[] = "bar2";
789 constexpr char largest[] = "foo2";
790 constexpr uint64_t file_size = 2000;
791
792 Add(level, second_sst, smallest, largest, file_size, first_blob);
793 }
794
795 {
796 constexpr char smallest[] = "bar3";
797 constexpr char largest[] = "foo3";
798 constexpr uint64_t file_size = 3000;
799
800 Add(level, third_sst, smallest, largest, file_size, third_blob);
801 }
802
803 {
804 constexpr uint64_t total_blob_count = 10;
805 constexpr uint64_t total_blob_bytes = 100000;
806 constexpr uint64_t garbage_blob_count = 2;
807 constexpr uint64_t garbage_blob_bytes = 15000;
808
809 AddBlob(first_blob, total_blob_count, total_blob_bytes,

811 garbage_blob_count, garbage_blob_bytes);
812 }
813
814 {
815 constexpr uint64_t total_blob_count = 4;
816 constexpr uint64_t total_blob_bytes = 400000;
817 constexpr uint64_t garbage_blob_count = 3;
818 constexpr uint64_t garbage_blob_bytes = 235000;
819
820 AddBlob(second_blob, total_blob_count, total_blob_bytes,
821 BlobFileMetaData::LinkedSsts{}, garbage_blob_count,
822 garbage_blob_bytes);
823 }
824
825 {
826 constexpr uint64_t total_blob_count = 20;
827 constexpr uint64_t total_blob_bytes = 1000000;
828 constexpr uint64_t garbage_blob_count = 8;
829 constexpr uint64_t garbage_blob_bytes = 123456;
830
831 AddBlob(third_blob, total_blob_count, total_blob_bytes,
832 BlobFileMetaData::LinkedSsts{third_sst}, garbage_blob_count,
833 garbage_blob_bytes);
834 }
835
836 {
837 constexpr uint64_t total_blob_count = 128;
838 constexpr uint64_t total_blob_bytes = 789012345;
839 constexpr uint64_t garbage_blob_count = 67;
840 constexpr uint64_t garbage_blob_bytes = 88888888;
841
842 AddBlob(fourth_blob, total_blob_count, total_blob_bytes,
843 BlobFileMetaData::LinkedSsts{}, garbage_blob_count,
844 garbage_blob_bytes);
845 }
846
847 UpdateVersionStorageInfo();
848
849 assert(vstorage_.num_levels() > 0);
850 const auto& level_files = vstorage_.LevelFiles(level);
851
852 assert(level_files.size() == 3);
853 assert(level_files[0] && level_files[0]->fd.GetNumber() == first_sst);
854 assert(level_files[1] && level_files[1]->fd.GetNumber() == second_sst);
855 assert(level_files[2] && level_files[2]->fd.GetNumber() == third_sst);
856
857 // No blob files eligible for GC due to the age cutoff
858
859 {
860 constexpr double age_cutoff = 0.1;
861 constexpr double force_threshold = 0.0;
862 vstorage_.ComputeFilesMarkedForForcedBlobGC(
863 age_cutoff, force_threshold, /*enable_blob_garbage_collection=*/true);
864
865 ASSERT_TRUE(vstorage_.FilesMarkedForForcedBlobGC().empty());
866 }
867
868 // Overall garbage ratio of eligible files is below threshold
869
870 {
871 constexpr double age_cutoff = 0.5;
872 constexpr double force_threshold = 0.6;
873 vstorage_.ComputeFilesMarkedForForcedBlobGC(
874 age_cutoff, force_threshold, /*enable_blob_garbage_collection=*/true);
875
876 ASSERT_TRUE(vstorage_.FilesMarkedForForcedBlobGC().empty());
877 }
878
879 // Overall garbage ratio of eligible files meets threshold
880
881 {
882 constexpr double age_cutoff = 0.5;
883 constexpr double force_threshold = 0.5;
884 vstorage_.ComputeFilesMarkedForForcedBlobGC(
885 age_cutoff, force_threshold, /*enable_blob_garbage_collection=*/true);
886
887 auto ssts_to_be_compacted = vstorage_.FilesMarkedForForcedBlobGC();
888 ASSERT_EQ(ssts_to_be_compacted.size(), 2);
889
890 std::sort(ssts_to_be_compacted.begin(), ssts_to_be_compacted.end(),
891 [](const std::pair<int, FileMetaData*>& lhs,
892 const std::pair<int, FileMetaData*>& rhs) {
893 assert(lhs.second);
894 assert(rhs.second);
895 return lhs.second->fd.GetNumber() < rhs.second->fd.GetNumber();
896 });
897
898 const autovector<std::pair<int, FileMetaData*>>
899 expected_ssts_to_be_compacted{{level, level_files[0]},
900 {level, level_files[1]}};
901
902 ASSERT_EQ(ssts_to_be_compacted[0], expected_ssts_to_be_compacted[0]);
903 ASSERT_EQ(ssts_to_be_compacted[1], expected_ssts_to_be_compacted[1]);
904 }

958class FindLevelFileTest : public testing::Test {
959 public:
960 LevelFilesBrief file_level_;
961 bool disjoint_sorted_files_;
962 Arena arena_;
963
964 FindLevelFileTest() : disjoint_sorted_files_(true) {}
965
966 ~FindLevelFileTest() override = default;
967
968 void LevelFileInit(size_t num = 0) {
969 char* mem = arena_.AllocateAligned(num * sizeof(FdWithKeyRange));
970 file_level_.files = new (mem) FdWithKeyRange[num];
971 file_level_.num_files = 0;
972 }
973
974 void Add(const char* smallest, const char* largest,
975 SequenceNumber smallest_seq = 100,
976 SequenceNumber largest_seq = 100) {
977 InternalKey smallest_key = InternalKey(smallest, smallest_seq, kTypeValue);
978 InternalKey largest_key = InternalKey(largest, largest_seq, kTypeValue);
979
980 Slice smallest_slice = smallest_key.Encode();
981 Slice largest_slice = largest_key.Encode();
982
983 char* mem =
984 arena_.AllocateAligned(smallest_slice.size() + largest_slice.size());
985 memcpy(mem, smallest_slice.data(), smallest_slice.size());
986 memcpy(mem + smallest_slice.size(), largest_slice.data(),
987 largest_slice.size());
988
989 // add to file_level_
990 size_t num = file_level_.num_files;
991 auto& file = file_level_.files[num];
992 file.fd = FileDescriptor(num + 1, 0, 0);
993 file.smallest_key = Slice(mem, smallest_slice.size());
994 file.largest_key = Slice(mem + smallest_slice.size(), largest_slice.size());
995 file_level_.num_files++;
996 }
997
998 int Find(const char* key) {
999 InternalKey target(key, 100, kTypeValue);
1000 InternalKeyComparator cmp(BytewiseComparator());
1001 return FindFile(cmp, file_level_, target.Encode());
1002 }
1003
1004 bool Overlaps(const char* smallest, const char* largest) {
1005 InternalKeyComparator cmp(BytewiseComparator());
1006 Slice s(smallest != nullptr ? smallest : "");
1007 Slice l(largest != nullptr ? largest : "");
1008 return SomeFileOverlapsRange(cmp, disjoint_sorted_files_, file_level_,
1009 (smallest != nullptr ? &s : nullptr),
1010 (largest != nullptr ? &l : nullptr));
1011 }
1012};
1013
1014TEST_F(FindLevelFileTest, LevelEmpty) {
1015 LevelFileInit(0);
1016
1017 ASSERT_EQ(0, Find("foo"));
1018 ASSERT_TRUE(!Overlaps("a", "z"));
1019 ASSERT_TRUE(!Overlaps(nullptr, "z"));
1020 ASSERT_TRUE(!Overlaps("a", nullptr));
1021 ASSERT_TRUE(!Overlaps(nullptr, nullptr));
1022}

1212 protected:
1213 virtual void PrepareManifest(
1214 std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor>* column_families,
1215 SequenceNumber* last_seqno, std::unique_ptr<log::Writer>* log_writer) {
1216 assert(column_families != nullptr);
1217 assert(last_seqno != nullptr);
1218 assert(log_writer != nullptr);
1219 ASSERT_OK(
1220 SetIdentityFile(WriteOptions(), env_, dbname_, Temperature::kUnknown));
1221 VersionEdit new_db;
1222 if (db_options_.write_dbid_to_manifest) {
1223 DBOptions tmp_db_options;
1224 tmp_db_options.env = env_;
1225 std::unique_ptr<DBImpl> impl(new DBImpl(tmp_db_options, dbname_));
1226 std::string db_id;
1227 ASSERT_OK(impl->GetDbIdentityFromIdentityFile(IOOptions(), &db_id));
1228 new_db.SetDBId(db_id);
1229 }
1230 new_db.SetLogNumber(0);
1231 new_db.SetNextFile(2);
1232 new_db.SetLastSequence(0);
1233
1234 const std::vector<std::string> cf_names = {
1235 kDefaultColumnFamilyName, kColumnFamilyName1, kColumnFamilyName2,
1236 kColumnFamilyName3};
1237 const int kInitialNumOfCfs = static_cast<int>(cf_names.size());
1238 autovector<VersionEdit> new_cfs;
1239 uint64_t last_seq = 1;
1240 uint32_t cf_id = 1;
1241 for (int i = 1; i != kInitialNumOfCfs; ++i) {
1242 VersionEdit new_cf;
1243 new_cf.AddColumnFamily(cf_names[i]);
1244 new_cf.SetColumnFamily(cf_id++);
1245 new_cf.SetLogNumber(0);
1246 new_cf.SetNextFile(2);
1247 new_cf.SetLastSequence(last_seq++);
1248 new_cfs.emplace_back(new_cf);
1249 }
1250 *last_seqno = last_seq;
1251 num_initial_edits_ = static_cast<int>(new_cfs.size() + 1);
1252 std::unique_ptr<WritableFileWriter> file_writer;
1253 const std::string manifest = DescriptorFileName(dbname_, 1);
1254 const auto& fs = env_->GetFileSystem();
1255 Status s = WritableFileWriter::Create(
1256 fs, manifest, fs->OptimizeForManifestWrite(env_options_), &file_writer,
1257 nullptr);
1258 ASSERT_OK(s);
1259 {
1260 log_writer->reset(new log::Writer(std::move(file_writer), 0, false));
1261 std::string record;
1262 new_db.EncodeTo(&record);
1263 s = (*log_writer)->AddRecord(WriteOptions(), record);
1264 for (const auto& e : new_cfs) {
1265 record.clear();
1266 e.EncodeTo(&record);
1267 s = (*log_writer)->AddRecord(WriteOptions(), record);
1268 ASSERT_OK(s);
1269 }
1270 }
1271 ASSERT_OK(s);
1272
1273 cf_options_.table_factory = table_factory_;
1274 for (const auto& cf_name : cf_names) {
1275 column_families->emplace_back(cf_name, cf_options_);
1276 }
1277 }

1280 uint64_t file_number;
1281 std::string column_family;
1282 std::string key; // the only key
1283 int level = 0;

1287 SstInfo(uint64_t file_num, const std::string& cf_name,
1288 const std::string& _key,
1289 uint64_t _epoch_number = kUnknownEpochNumber,
1290 bool _file_missing = false,

1308 // Create dummy sst, return their metadata. Note that only file name and size
1309 // are used.
1310 void CreateDummyTableFiles(const std::vector<SstInfo>& file_infos,
1311 std::vector<FileMetaData>* file_metas) {
1312 assert(file_metas != nullptr);
1313 for (const auto& info : file_infos) {
1314 uint64_t file_num = info.file_number;
1315 std::string fname = MakeTableFileName(dbname_, file_num);
1316 std::unique_ptr<FSWritableFile> file;
1317 Status s = fs_->NewWritableFile(fname, FileOptions(), &file, nullptr);
1318 ASSERT_OK(s);
1319 std::unique_ptr<WritableFileWriter> fwriter(new WritableFileWriter(
1320 std::move(file), fname, FileOptions(), env_->GetSystemClock().get()));
1321 InternalTblPropCollFactories internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories;
1322
1323 const ReadOptions read_options;
1324 const WriteOptions write_options;
1325 std::unique_ptr<TableBuilder> builder(table_factory_->NewTableBuilder(
1326 TableBuilderOptions(
1327 immutable_options_, mutable_cf_options_, read_options,
1328 write_options, InternalKeyComparator(options_.comparator),
1329 &internal_tbl_prop_coll_factories, kNoCompression,
1330 CompressionOptions(),
1331 TablePropertiesCollectorFactory::Context::kUnknownColumnFamily,
1332 info.column_family, info.level, kUnknownNewestKeyTime),
1333 fwriter.get()));
1334 InternalKey ikey(info.key, 0, ValueType::kTypeValue);
1335 builder->Add(ikey.Encode(), "value");
1336 ASSERT_OK(builder->Finish());
1337 ASSERT_OK(fwriter->Flush(IOOptions()));
1338 uint64_t file_size = 0;
1339 s = fs_->GetFileSize(fname, IOOptions(), &file_size, nullptr);
1340 ASSERT_OK(s);
1341 ASSERT_NE(0, file_size);
1342 file_metas->emplace_back(
1343 file_num, /*file_path_id=*/0, file_size, ikey, ikey, 0, 0, false,
1344 Temperature::kUnknown, info.oldest_blob_file_number, 0, 0,
1345 info.epoch_number, kUnknownFileChecksum, kUnknownFileChecksumFuncName,
1346 kNullUniqueId64x2, 0, 0,
1347 /* user_defined_timestamps_persisted */ true);
1348 if (info.file_missing) {
1349 ASSERT_OK(fs_->DeleteFile(fname, IOOptions(), nullptr));
1350 }
1351 }

1717TEST_F(VersionSetTest, ObsoleteBlobFile) {
1718 // Initialize the database and add a blob file that is entirely garbage
1719 // and thus can immediately be marked obsolete.
1720 NewDB();
1721
1722 VersionEdit edit;
1723
1724 constexpr uint64_t blob_file_number = 234;
1725 constexpr uint64_t total_blob_count = 555;
1726 constexpr uint64_t total_blob_bytes = 66666;
1727 constexpr char checksum_method[] = "CRC32";
1728 constexpr char checksum_value[] = "\x3d\x87\xff\x57";
1729
1730 edit.AddBlobFile(blob_file_number, total_blob_count, total_blob_bytes,
1731 checksum_method, checksum_value);
1732
1733 edit.AddBlobFileGarbage(blob_file_number, total_blob_count, total_blob_bytes);
1734
1735 mutex_.Lock();
1736 Status s = versions_->LogAndApply(
1737 versions_->GetColumnFamilySet()->GetDefault(), mutable_cf_options_,
1738 read_options_, write_options_, &edit, &mutex_, nullptr);
1739 mutex_.Unlock();
1740
1741 ASSERT_OK(s);
1742
1743 // Make sure blob files from the pending number range are not returned
1744 // as obsolete.
1745 {
1746 std::vector<ObsoleteFileInfo> table_files;
1747 std::vector<ObsoleteBlobFileInfo> blob_files;
1748 std::vector<std::string> manifest_files;
1749 constexpr uint64_t min_pending_output = blob_file_number;
1750
1751 versions_->GetObsoleteFiles(&table_files, &blob_files, &manifest_files,
1752 min_pending_output);
1753
1754 ASSERT_TRUE(blob_files.empty());
1755 }
1756
1757 // Make sure the blob file is returned as obsolete if it's not in the pending
1758 // range.
1759 {
1760 std::vector<ObsoleteFileInfo> table_files;
1761 std::vector<ObsoleteBlobFileInfo> blob_files;
1762 std::vector<std::string> manifest_files;
1763 constexpr uint64_t min_pending_output = blob_file_number + 1;
1764
1765 versions_->GetObsoleteFiles(&table_files, &blob_files, &manifest_files,
1766 min_pending_output);
1767
1768 ASSERT_EQ(blob_files.size(), 1);
1769 ASSERT_EQ(blob_files[0].GetBlobFileNumber(), blob_file_number);
1770 }
1771
1772 // Make sure it's not returned a second time.
1773 {
1774 std::vector<ObsoleteFileInfo> table_files;
1775 std::vector<ObsoleteBlobFileInfo> blob_files;
1776 std::vector<std::string> manifest_files;
1777 constexpr uint64_t min_pending_output = blob_file_number + 1;
1778
1779 versions_->GetObsoleteFiles(&table_files, &blob_files, &manifest_files,

2439 void GenVersionEditsToSetFullHistoryTsLow(
2440 const std::vector<uint64_t>& ts_lbs) {
2441 for (const auto ts_lb : ts_lbs) {
2442 VersionEdit* edit = new VersionEdit;
2443 edit->SetColumnFamily(cfd_->GetID());
2444 std::string ts_str = test::EncodeInt(ts_lb);
2445 edit->SetFullHistoryTsLow(ts_str);
2446 edits_.emplace_back(edit);
2447 }
2448 }
2449
2450 void VerifyFullHistoryTsLow(uint64_t expected_ts_low) {
2451 std::unique_ptr<VersionSet> vset(new VersionSet(
2452 dbname_, &db_options_, env_options_, table_cache_.get(),
2453 &write_buffer_manager_, &write_controller_,
2454 /*block_cache_tracer=*/nullptr, /*io_tracer=*/nullptr,
2455 /*db_id=*/"", /*db_session_id=*/"", /*daily_offpeak_time_utc=*/"",
2456 /*error_handler=*/nullptr, /*read_only=*/false));
2457 ASSERT_OK(vset->Recover(column_families_, /*read_only=*/false,
2458 /*db_id=*/nullptr));
2459 for (auto* cfd : *(vset->GetColumnFamilySet())) {
2460 ASSERT_NE(nullptr, cfd);
2461 if (cfd->GetName() == kNewCfName) {
2462 ASSERT_EQ(test::EncodeInt(expected_ts_low), cfd->GetFullHistoryTsLow());
2463 } else {
2464 ASSERT_TRUE(cfd->GetFullHistoryTsLow().empty());
2465 }
2466 }
2467 }
2468
2469 void DoTest(const std::vector<uint64_t>& ts_lbs) {
2470 if (ts_lbs.empty()) {
2471 return;
2472 }
2473
2474 GenVersionEditsToSetFullHistoryTsLow(ts_lbs);
2475
2476 Status s;
2477 mutex_.Lock();
2478 s = versions_->LogAndApply(cfd_, *(cfd_->GetLatestMutableCFOptions()),
2479 read_options_, write_options_, edits_, &mutex_,
2480 nullptr);
2481 mutex_.Unlock();
2482 ASSERT_OK(s);
2483 VerifyFullHistoryTsLow(*std::max_element(ts_lbs.begin(), ts_lbs.end()));
2484 }
2485
2486 protected:
2487 ColumnFamilyData* cfd_{nullptr};
2488 // edits_ must contain and own pointers to heap-alloc VersionEdit objects.
2489 autovector<VersionEdit*> edits_;
2490
2491 private:
2492 const ReadOptions read_options_;
2493};

2900class AtomicGroupBestEffortRecoveryTest : public VersionSetAtomicGroupTest {
2901 public:
2902 AtomicGroupBestEffortRecoveryTest()
2903 : VersionSetAtomicGroupTest("atomic_group_best_effort_recovery_test") {}

2905
2906TEST_F(AtomicGroupBestEffortRecoveryTest,
2907 HandleAtomicGroupUpdatesValidInitially) {
2908 // One AtomicGroup contains updates that are valid at the outset.
2909 std::vector<SstInfo> file_infos;
2910 for (int cfid = 0; cfid < kNumColumnFamilies; cfid++) {
2911 int file_number = 10 + cfid;
2912 file_infos.emplace_back(file_number, column_families_[cfid].name,
2913 "" /* key */, 0 /* level */,
2914 file_number /* epoch_number */);
2915 }
2916
2917 std::vector<FileMetaData> file_metas;
2918 CreateDummyTableFiles(file_infos, &file_metas);
2919
2920 edits_.clear();
2921 for (int cfid = 0; cfid < kNumColumnFamilies; cfid++) {
2922 edits_.emplace_back();
2923 edits_.back().SetColumnFamily(cfid);
2924 edits_.back().AddFile(0 /* level */, file_metas[cfid]);
2925 edits_.back().SetLastSequence(++last_seqno_);
2926 edits_.back().MarkAtomicGroup(kNumColumnFamilies - 1 -
2927 cfid /* remaining_entries */);
2928 }
2929 AddNewEditsToLog(kNumColumnFamilies);
2930

3319class VersionSetTestDropOneCF : public VersionSetTestBase,
3320 public testing::TestWithParam<std::string> {
3321 public:
3322 VersionSetTestDropOneCF()
3323 : VersionSetTestBase("version_set_test_drop_one_cf") {}
3324};
3325
3326// This test simulates the following execution sequence
3327// Time thread1 bg_flush_thr
3328// | Prepare version edits (e1,e2,e3) for atomic
3329// | flush cf1, cf2, cf3
3330// | Enqueue e to drop cfi
3331// | to manifest_writers_
3332// | Enqueue (e1,e2,e3) to manifest_writers_
3333// |
3334// | Apply e,
3335// | cfi.IsDropped() is true
3336// | Apply (e1,e2,e3),
3337// | since cfi.IsDropped() == true, we need to
3338// | drop ei and write the rest to MANIFEST.
3339// V
3340//
3341// Repeat the test for i = 1, 2, 3 to simulate dropping the first, middle and
3342// last column family in an atomic group.
3343TEST_P(VersionSetTestDropOneCF, HandleDroppedColumnFamilyInAtomicGroup) {
3344 const ReadOptions read_options;
3345 const WriteOptions write_options;
3346
3347 std::vector<ColumnFamilyDescriptor> column_families;
3348 SequenceNumber last_seqno;
3349 std::unique_ptr<log::Writer> log_writer;
3350 PrepareManifest(&column_families, &last_seqno, &log_writer);
3351 CreateCurrentFile();
3352
3353 EXPECT_OK(versions_->Recover(column_families, false /* read_only */));
3354 EXPECT_EQ(column_families.size(),
3355 versions_->GetColumnFamilySet()->NumberOfColumnFamilies());
3356
3357 const int kAtomicGroupSize = 3;
3358 const std::vector<std::string> non_default_cf_names = {
3359 kColumnFamilyName1, kColumnFamilyName2, kColumnFamilyName3};
3360
3361 // Drop one column family
3362 VersionEdit drop_cf_edit;
3363 drop_cf_edit.DropColumnFamily();
3364 const std::string cf_to_drop_name(GetParam());
3365 auto cfd_to_drop =
3366 versions_->GetColumnFamilySet()->GetColumnFamily(cf_to_drop_name);
3367 ASSERT_NE(nullptr, cfd_to_drop);
3368 // Increase its refcount because cfd_to_drop is used later, and we need to
3369 // prevent it from being deleted.
3370 cfd_to_drop->Ref();
3371 drop_cf_edit.SetColumnFamily(cfd_to_drop->GetID());
3372 mutex_.Lock();
3373 Status s = versions_->LogAndApply(
3374 cfd_to_drop, *cfd_to_drop->GetLatestMutableCFOptions(), read_options,
3375 write_options, &drop_cf_edit, &mutex_, nullptr);
3376 mutex_.Unlock();
3377 ASSERT_OK(s);
3378
3379 std::vector<VersionEdit> edits(kAtomicGroupSize);
3380 uint32_t remaining = kAtomicGroupSize;
3381 size_t i = 0;
3382 autovector<ColumnFamilyData*> cfds;
3383 autovector<const MutableCFOptions*> mutable_cf_options_list;
3384 autovector<autovector<VersionEdit*>> edit_lists;
3385 for (const auto& cf_name : non_default_cf_names) {
3386 auto cfd = (cf_name != cf_to_drop_name)
3387 ? versions_->GetColumnFamilySet()->GetColumnFamily(cf_name)
3388 : cfd_to_drop;
3389 ASSERT_NE(nullptr, cfd);
3390 cfds.push_back(cfd);
3391 mutable_cf_options_list.emplace_back(cfd->GetLatestMutableCFOptions());
3392 edits[i].SetColumnFamily(cfd->GetID());
3393 edits[i].SetLogNumber(0);
3394 edits[i].SetNextFile(2);
3395 edits[i].MarkAtomicGroup(--remaining);
3396 edits[i].SetLastSequence(last_seqno++);
3397 autovector<VersionEdit*> tmp_edits;
3398 tmp_edits.push_back(&edits[i]);
3399 edit_lists.emplace_back(tmp_edits);
3400 ++i;
3401 }
3402 int called = 0;
3403 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
3404 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->ClearAllCallBacks();
3405 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->SetCallBack(
3406 "VersionSet::ProcessManifestWrites:CheckOneAtomicGroup", [&](void* arg) {
3407 std::vector<VersionEdit*>* tmp_edits =
3408 static_cast<std::vector<VersionEdit*>*>(arg);
3409 EXPECT_EQ(kAtomicGroupSize - 1, tmp_edits->size());
3410 for (const auto e : *tmp_edits) {
3411 bool found = false;
3412 for (const auto& e2 : edits) {
3413 if (&e2 == e) {
3414 found = true;
3415 break;
3416 }
3417 }
3418 ASSERT_TRUE(found);
3419 }
3420 ++called;
3421 });
3422 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
3423 mutex_.Lock();
3424 s = versions_->LogAndApply(cfds, mutable_cf_options_list, read_options,
3425 write_options, edit_lists, &mutex_, nullptr);
3426 mutex_.Unlock();
3427 ASSERT_OK(s);
3428 ASSERT_EQ(1, called);
3429 cfd_to_drop->UnrefAndTryDelete();
3430}

3892 // This method updates last_sequence_.
3893 void WriteFileAdditionAndDeletionToManifest(
3894 uint32_t cf, const std::vector<std::pair<int, FileMetaData>>& added_files,
3895 const std::vector<std::pair<int, uint64_t>>& deleted_files,
3896 const std::vector<BlobFileAddition>& blob_files = {}) {
3897 VersionEdit edit;
3898 edit.SetColumnFamily(cf);
3899 for (const auto& elem : added_files) {
3900 int level = elem.first;
3901 edit.AddFile(level, elem.second);
3902 }
3903 for (const auto& elem : deleted_files) {
3904 int level = elem.first;
3905 edit.DeleteFile(level, elem.second);
3906 }
3907 for (const auto& elem : blob_files) {
3908 edit.AddBlobFile(elem);
3909 }
3910 edit.SetLastSequence(last_seqno_);
3911 ++last_seqno_;
3912 assert(log_writer_.get() != nullptr);
3913 std::string record;
3914 ASSERT_TRUE(edit.EncodeTo(&record, 0 /* ts_sz */));
3915 Status s = log_writer_->AddRecord(WriteOptions(), record);
3916 ASSERT_OK(s);
3917 }

4370class ChargeFileMetadataTestWithParam
4371 : public ChargeFileMetadataTest,
4372 public testing::WithParamInterface<CacheEntryRoleOptions::Decision> {
4373 public:
4374 ChargeFileMetadataTestWithParam() = default;
4375};
4376
4377INSTANTIATE_TEST_CASE_P(
4378 ChargeFileMetadataTestWithParam, ChargeFileMetadataTestWithParam,
4379 ::testing::Values(CacheEntryRoleOptions::Decision::kEnabled,
4380 CacheEntryRoleOptions::Decision::kDisabled));
4381
4382TEST_P(ChargeFileMetadataTestWithParam, Basic) {
4383 Options options;
4384 options.level_compaction_dynamic_level_bytes = false;
4385 BlockBasedTableOptions table_options;
4386 CacheEntryRoleOptions::Decision charge_file_metadata = GetParam();
4387 table_options.cache_usage_options.options_overrides.insert(
4388 {CacheEntryRole::kFileMetadata, {/*.charged = */ charge_file_metadata}});
4389 std::shared_ptr<TargetCacheChargeTrackingCache<CacheEntryRole::kFileMetadata>>
4390 file_metadata_charge_only_cache = std::make_shared<
4391 TargetCacheChargeTrackingCache<CacheEntryRole::kFileMetadata>>(
4392 NewLRUCache(
4393 4 * CacheReservationManagerImpl<
4394 CacheEntryRole::kFileMetadata>::GetDummyEntrySize(),
4395 0 /* num_shard_bits */, true /* strict_capacity_limit */));
4396 table_options.block_cache = file_metadata_charge_only_cache;
4397 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
4398 options.create_if_missing = true;
4399 options.disable_auto_compactions = true;
4400 DestroyAndReopen(options);
4401
4402 // Create 128 file metadata, each of which is roughly 1024 bytes.
4403 // This results in 1 *
4404 // CacheReservationManagerImpl<CacheEntryRole::kFileMetadata>::GetDummyEntrySize()
4405 // cache reservation for file metadata.
4406 for (int i = 1; i <= 128; ++i) {
4407 ASSERT_OK(Put(std::string(1024, 'a'), "va"));
4408 ASSERT_OK(Put("b", "vb"));
4409 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
4410 }
4411 if (charge_file_metadata == CacheEntryRoleOptions::Decision::kEnabled) {
4412 EXPECT_EQ(file_metadata_charge_only_cache->GetCacheCharge(),
4413 1 * CacheReservationManagerImpl<
4414 CacheEntryRole::kFileMetadata>::GetDummyEntrySize());
4415
4416 } else {
4417 EXPECT_EQ(file_metadata_charge_only_cache->GetCacheCharge(), 0);
4418 }
4419
4420 // Create another 128 file metadata.
4421 // This increases the file metadata cache reservation to 2 *
4422 // CacheReservationManagerImpl<CacheEntryRole::kFileMetadata>::GetDummyEntrySize().
4423 for (int i = 1; i <= 128; ++i) {
4424 ASSERT_OK(Put(std::string(1024, 'a'), "vva"));
4425 ASSERT_OK(Put("b", "vvb"));
4426 ASSERT_OK(Flush());
4427 }
4428 if (charge_file_metadata == CacheEntryRoleOptions::Decision::kEnabled) {
4429 EXPECT_EQ(file_metadata_charge_only_cache->GetCacheCharge(),
4430 2 * CacheReservationManagerImpl<
4431 CacheEntryRole::kFileMetadata>::GetDummyEntrySize());
4432 } else {
4433 EXPECT_EQ(file_metadata_charge_only_cache->GetCacheCharge(), 0);
4434 }
4435 // Compaction will create 1 new file metadata, obsolete and delete all 256
4436 // file metadata above. This results in 1 *
4437 // CacheReservationManagerImpl<CacheEntryRole::kFileMetadata>::GetDummyEntrySize()
4438 // cache reservation for file metadata.
4439 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->LoadDependency(
4440 {{"DBImpl::BackgroundCallCompaction:PurgedObsoleteFiles",
4441 "ChargeFileMetadataTestWithParam::"
4442 "PreVerifyingCacheReservationRelease"}});
4443 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->EnableProcessing();
4444 ASSERT_OK(db_->CompactRange(CompactRangeOptions(), nullptr, nullptr));
4445 ASSERT_EQ("0,1", FilesPerLevel(0));
4446 TEST_SYNC_POINT(
4447 "ChargeFileMetadataTestWithParam::PreVerifyingCacheReservationRelease");
4448 if (charge_file_metadata == CacheEntryRoleOptions::Decision::kEnabled) {
4449 EXPECT_EQ(file_metadata_charge_only_cache->GetCacheCharge(),
4450 1 * CacheReservationManagerImpl<
4451 CacheEntryRole::kFileMetadata>::GetDummyEntrySize());
4452 } else {
4453 EXPECT_EQ(file_metadata_charge_only_cache->GetCacheCharge(), 0);
4454 }
4455 SyncPoint::GetInstance()->DisableProcessing();
4456
4457 // Destroying the db will delete the remaining 1 new file metadata
4458 // This results in no cache reservation for file metadata.
4459 Destroy(options);
4460 EXPECT_EQ(file_metadata_charge_only_cache->GetCacheCharge(),
4461 0 * CacheReservationManagerImpl<
4462 CacheEntryRole::kFileMetadata>::GetDummyEntrySize());
4463
4464 // Reopen the db with a smaller cache in order to test failure in allocating
4465 // file metadata due to memory limit based on cache capacity
4466 file_metadata_charge_only_cache = std::make_shared<
4467 TargetCacheChargeTrackingCache<CacheEntryRole::kFileMetadata>>(
4468 NewLRUCache(1 * CacheReservationManagerImpl<
4469 CacheEntryRole::kFileMetadata>::GetDummyEntrySize(),
4470 0 /* num_shard_bits */, true /* strict_capacity_limit */));
4471 table_options.block_cache = file_metadata_charge_only_cache;
4472 options.table_factory.reset(NewBlockBasedTableFactory(table_options));
4473 Reopen(options);
4474 ASSERT_OK(Put(std::string(1024, 'a'), "va"));
4475 ASSERT_OK(Put("b", "vb"));
4476 Status s = Flush();
4477 if (charge_file_metadata == CacheEntryRoleOptions::Decision::kEnabled) {
4478 EXPECT_TRUE(s.IsMemoryLimit());
4479 EXPECT_TRUE(s.ToString().find(
4480 kCacheEntryRoleToCamelString[static_cast<std::uint32_t>(
4481 CacheEntryRole::kFileMetadata)]) != std::string::npos);
4482 EXPECT_TRUE(s.ToString().find("memory limit based on cache capacity") !=
4483 std::string::npos);
4484 } else {
4485 EXPECT_TRUE(s.ok());
4486 }
4487}
